ATTRIBUTION NOTICE:

This software implements the Golden Universe (GU) theoretical framework for 
deriving particle masses and fundamental constants from first principles. 
Key theoretical breakthroughs include:

1. The corrected resonance condition using round(N/φ²) instead of floor(N/φ²)
2. The discovery of resonance duality between even k_res (resonant) and odd 
   k_res (anti-resonant) particles
3. Sub-percent precision particle mass derivations from geometric first 
   principles
4. Newton's gravitational constant G_N derived from the electron mass with 
   47 ppm precision and ZERO fitted parameters
5. The Seeley-DeWitt coefficient c_R = 1.247 derived from SU(5)+SUSY field 
   content, simultaneously satisfying the cosmological constant constraint
6. The first derivation of the fine structure constant 1/137 from pure 
   mathematics: α_EM = (e^φ/π²)/70

When using this software in academic or commercial work, please cite:
- The Golden Universe Theory framework

For academic publications, please reference the theoretical foundations and
acknowledge the open source nature of this implementation.